<head>DIVORCE</head>
    <list type="altnames">
<item>DISSOLVE ONE'S MARRIAGE</item>
<item>ANNUL ONE'S MARRIAGE</item>
<item>END ONE'S MARRIAGE</item>
<item>GET A DIVORCE</item>
    </list>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">離婚</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>STOP one's MARRIAGE.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The standard word for divorce refers only to the husband sending away his wife: chū 出.</p>
<p>NB: Xiū 休 is post-Han, Tang.</p>
        </div>
